---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout pageTitle='Favorite Things - Music'>
  <div class='content-wrapper'>
    <div class='headline'>
      <p class='smaller center'>
        Some of my favorite music, <a href='/books'>books</a>
        and <a href='/other-favorites'>other things</a> on the web.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div id='music-grid'>
      <div class='card-wrapper'>
        <a href='https://youtu.be/FszBbfxDn4o' target='_blank'>
          <div class='m_load_here'>
            <img
              class='video-thumbnail'
              src='https://img.youtube.com/vi/FszBbfxDn4o/hqdefault.jpg'
              alt='YouTube Video'
            />
          </div>
          <div class='video-description'>
            Here is John Legend's wonderful cover of Springsteen's <strong
              >Dancing in the Dark</strong
            >. And because he is on Howard Stern, he sounds amazing. This one
            brought out the lyrics to me more than the original.
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class='card-wrapper'>
        <a href='https://youtu.be/-wVWjl9Kq6U' target='_blank'>
          <div class='m_load_here'>
            <img
              class='video-thumbnail'
              src='https://img.youtube.com/vi/-wVWjl9Kq6U/hqdefault.jpg'
              alt='YouTube Video'
            />
          </div>
          <div class='video-description'>
            My wife introduced me to the <strong>Tedeschi Trucks Band,</strong> a
            great band headed by singer Susan Tedeschi and her husband, guitarist
            Derek Trucks. I could listen for hours to any of their performances of
            <strong>Midnight in Harlem</strong>.
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class='card-wrapper'>
        <a href='https://youtu.be/20Ov0cDPZy8' target='_blank'>
          <div class='m_load_here'>
            <img
              class='video-thumbnail'
              src='https://img.youtube.com/vi/20Ov0cDPZy8/hqdefault.jpg'
              alt='YouTube Video'
            />
          </div>
          <div class='video-description'>
            I loved Tom Petty's album Full Moon Fever back in the old days, but <strong
              >John Mayer</strong
            > (with some help) brings something wonderful to <strong
              >Free Fallin'</strong
            >. Really good.
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class='card-wrapper'>
        <a href='https://youtu.be/jVLNB3d-2cA' target='_blank'>
          <div class='m_load_here'>
            <img
              class='video-thumbnail'
              src='https://img.youtube.com/vi/jVLNB3d-2cA/hqdefault.jpg'
              alt='YouTube Video'
            />
          </div>
          <div class='video-description'>
            I mentioned that every musical artist sounds great on Howard Stern.
            In my more emotional moments, I like to say that this cover of
            Fleetwood Mac's <strong>The Chain</strong> by
            <strong>The Highwomen</strong> is the greatest recording in history.
            It sounds SOOOO good.
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class='card-wrapper'>
        <a href='https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Er1GMEK9-hE' target='_blank'>
          <div class='m_load_here'>
            <img
              class='video-thumbnail'
              src='https://img.youtube.com/vi/Er1GMEK9-hE/hqdefault.jpg'
              alt='YouTube Video'
            />
          </div>
          <div class='video-description'>
            <strong>Prince</strong> was, among many other things, an amazing guitarist.
            Here he is live with just an acoustic guitar, owning his audience with
            talent and charm.
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class='card-wrapper'>
        <a href='https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gBrUU-DfihY' target='_blank'>
          <div class='m_load_here'>
            <img
              class='video-thumbnail'
              src='https://img.youtube.com/vi/gBrUU-DfihY/hqdefault.jpg'
              alt='YouTube Video'
            />
          </div>
          <div class='video-description'>
            <strong>Gettysburg</strong> is an 80s rocker from the not-very-well-known
            <strong>The Brandos</strong>. It's a great song and it always
            reminds me of a trip I took there with a friend back in college.
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class='card-wrapper'>
        <a href='https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QO5dcW0P75M' target='_blank'>
          <div class='m_load_here'>
            <img
              class='video-thumbnail'
              src='https://img.youtube.com/vi/QO5dcW0P75M/hqdefault.jpg'
              alt='YouTube Video'
            />
          </div>
          <div class='video-description'>
            <strong>Birth, School, Work, Death</strong> is some late New Wave by
            <strong>The Godfathers</strong> that really delivers a punch.
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class='card-wrapper'>
        <a href='https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iM4LzEcaTK0' target='_blank'>
          <div class='m_load_here'>
            <img
              class='video-thumbnail'
              src='https://img.youtube.com/vi/iM4LzEcaTK0/hqdefault.jpg'
              alt='YouTube Video'
            />
          </div>
          <div class='video-description'>
            Here is an astounding live version of <strong
              >New York State of Mind</strong
            > from the mid-to-late 70s, when <strong>Billy Joel</strong> was just
            begining his climb to massive popularity. <strong
              >Richie Cannata</strong
            > is the guy with the great sax solo here.
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class='card-wrapper'>
        <a href='https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NOwXqIFikAM' target='_blank'>
          <div class='m_load_here'>
            <img
              class='video-thumbnail'
              src='https://img.youtube.com/vi/NOwXqIFikAM/hqdefault.jpg'
              alt='YouTube Video'
            />
          </div>
          <div class='video-description'>
            This acoustic version of<strong> White Wedding</strong> is from 2001,
            and features
            <strong>Billy Idol</strong> in fine voice, but I'm especially impressed
            with the always great <strong>Steve Stevens</strong> on guitar.
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class='card-wrapper'>
        <a href='https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eQluGs2SFRs' target='_blank'>
          <div class='m_load_here'>
            <img
              class='video-thumbnail'
              src='https://img.youtube.com/vi/eQluGs2SFRs/hqdefault.jpg'
              alt='YouTube Video'
            />
          </div>
          <div class='video-description'>
            I somehow missed this, the best of all <strong>AC/DC</strong> tracks
            till it was featured over the credits of Jack Black's <em
              >School of Rock</em
            >, but <strong>It's a Long Way to the Top</strong> is now an all-time
            favorite.
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class='card-wrapper'>
        <a href='https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LFxOaDeJmXk' target='_blank'>
          <div class='m_load_here'>
            <img
              class='video-thumbnail'
              src='https://img.youtube.com/vi/LFxOaDeJmXk/hqdefault.jpg'
              alt='YouTube Video'
            />
          </div>
          <div class='video-description'>
            From the Kennedy Center Honors in 2012, here's the second-best
            recording of <strong> Stairway to Heaven</strong>. This performance
            is in honor of <strong>Led Zepplin</strong>, and features <strong
              >Ann and Nancy Wilson, Jason Bonham</strong
            > taking his father's place on drums, and a great choir.
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class='card-wrapper'>
        <a href='https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xpYHgbjOIq0' target='_blank'>
          <div class='m_load_here'>
            <img
              class='video-thumbnail'
              src='https://img.youtube.com/vi/xpYHgbjOIq0/hqdefault.jpg'
              alt='YouTube Video'
            />
          </div>
          <div class='video-description'>
            I love this. It's <strong>Fooling Yourself</strong> by <strong
              >Tommy Shaw</strong
            > backed up by the awesome
            <strong>Contemporary Youth Orchestra</strong>. Lots of joy on the
            faces of the performers and the audience. Watch the blonde girl in
            the crowd get caught up while Papaw beside her is transported back
            to when he saw
            <strong>Styx</strong> live in '78.
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <style>
    .card-wrapper {
      max-width: 480px;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
      background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.089);
      border-radius: 5px;
      border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);
    }
    .card-wrapper:hover {
      border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
    }
    #music-grid {
      display: grid;
      width: 90vw;
      max-width: 976px;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 50%);
      grid-template-rows: auto;
      grid-gap: 16px;
      margin: auto;
    }
    img.video-thumbnail {
      width: 100%;
      height: auto;
      max-width: 480px;
    }
    .video-description {
      padding: 10px;
    }
    #music-grid a,
    #music-grid a:hover {
      color: black;
    }

    @media (max-width: 767px) {
      .video-description {
        font-size: 14px;
      }
    }

    @media (max-width: 699px) {
      #music-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 100%;
        max-width: 480px;
      }
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
